 local PostgreSQL database.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"docker_image\",\n      \"image\": \"postgres:18-alpine\",\n      \"slug\": \"postgres\",\n      \"reason\": \"The library documentation shows normal doobie-postgres usage via Transactor.fromDriverManager with org.postgresql.Driver and jdbc:postgresql URLs, and the repository already allows this PostgreSQL image for JDBC/PostgreSQL tests.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"No extra Maven dependency is needed for ordinary doobie-postgres coverage. For Scala tests that summon Meta[java.time.ZonedDateTime], import doobie.implicits.javatimedrivernative.JavaZonedDateTimeMeta or avoid ZonedDateTime; doobie.postgres.implicits._ in 1.0.0-RC3 provides Instant, OffsetDateTime, LocalDateTime, LocalDate, LocalTime, and OffsetTime but not ZonedDateTime. Live database tests should create a JDBC transactor with org.postgresql.Driver and a jdbc:postgresql URL using the database/user/password configured when starting the declared local container.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"PostGIS mappings exist behind provided net.postgis:postgis-jdbc types; do not cover those unless intentionally adding that optional dependency and a PostGIS-capable database setup.\",\n    \"Docker-based tests must use the declared pre-pulled image and local container networking; CI will not permit ad-hoc image pulls.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0f24a5ded856bf2c016a2a7fef031c819792d073bec459be6e\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 927, "output": 887, "cacheRead": 49664, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 51478, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1781170141794, "responseId": "resp_0f24a5ded856bf2c016a2a7fdeb2948197aba307401d8f636c"}, "toolResults": []}
